current_contact.agency: San Bernardino County Sheriff Department - Coroner Division

case_address_found_1: Westbound Interstate 40, at mile post marker 75
case_circumstances: Jane Doe #10-04 was a passenger (1 of 10 occupants) in van transporting persons from Mexico which crashed while travelling westbound along Interstate 40 Freeway on July 18, 2004.  The woman was in possession of a fake Birth Certificate (per Mexican consulate) in the name of "Antonia Dominguez Juarez, DOB: 05/22/76, age 28."  Other names developed by people inquiring: "Maria Eugenia Martinez" (06/25/65), or possibly a woman from Guatamala.  Per one passenger, most of the people in the van were from Santa Lucia Del Camino, OAX, Mexico.  Nine of the occupants were picked up in Phoenix Arizona.
